OVERVIEW                                                    *thunderus-overview*
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Thunderus is a high-performance coding agent harness built in Rust. It attempts
to replicate the rigorous workflows of "Claude Code" and the "Codex CLI", but
packaged as a standalone, provider-agnostic TUI tool.

It is designed for developers who want an agent that works *in* their repos,
following strict "diff-first" and "shell-gated" safety protocols.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PHILOSOPHY                                                *thunderus-philosophy*
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1.  Harness > Chat
    The interface is a TUI work-bench, not a conversational UI.

2.  Shell-First
    "Anything in the shell" is usable, but gated by approval modes.

3.  Mixed-Initiative
    Seamless collaboration. If you type, the agent pauses. If you edit, the
    agent reconciles.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE                                                          *thunderus-usage*
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  $ thunder|thunderus|thndrs

  > Create a new component for the video player...

  [Drafting...]

  [Action] Create file `src/video.rs`? [y/N]

